This manual will assume that you know how to program the 
synthesizer.

    On starting up the main screen will be drawn from disc as will 
the menu and some starting data. When the disc has finished 
working you may start to use the program.

    Most of the screen is taken with 3 large white blocks these 
are used to create the envelopes the names of each is down the 
lefthand side. Beneath each name is a number this tells you how 
many steps you have. Some envelopes are so close that you can't 
see how many there are hence the need for these numbers. Across 
the top of each block there are three boxes. The leftmost marked 
ADD STEP inserts a step and of course SUBTRACT STEP removes a 
step. The third box will switch on the SUS step after pointing to 
this box with the mouse it will turn RED and you then select which 
step you wish to SUSTAIN by pointing at it. The number of the step 
you have chosen will then be displayed in the box and your SUS 
step line will turn green. To remove SUS point to box again. (NOTE 
you can't make the last step SUS).

    In order to move the envelope just point to the junction you 
wish to change press the left mouse button and move to the desired 
position to help set a certain value use the display at the bottom 
right which will display the current value as you move the mouse. 
You will know if the mouse has locked onto a junction because the 
arrow will change to a pointing finger. IMPORTANT NOTE THE 
ENVELOPES ARE ONLY IN INCREMENTS OF TWO TO ALLOW THE ENVELOPES TO 
BE DISPLAYED ON THE SCREEN. This will make no noticeable 
difference to the finished sound if copying a sound just round up 
or down.     To make things a little easier if editing and you 
just need to change the rate value hold down the LEFT SHIFT while 
selecting the junction you wish to alter, press ALTERNATE if you 
just wish to change the level    
    To select a WAVEFORM just point to box you want the top row is 
always switched on the bottom row can be on or off. To turn bottom 
row off point to wavefrom which is switched on. 
    To select the keyfollow just point to which value you require.

    If you are familiar with the CZ range you will know that we 
can have two voices, to set up the second voice frist select 
voice2 in the FILE 2 menu heading the page will look the same 
apart from any settings you have made. So that you know which 
VOICE you are editing at the top right there are two headings 
called VOICE  and SOUND, VOICE will show 1 or 2     SOUND 
indicates which SOUND or instrument you are editing in the range 1 
to 16. At the bottom is the name of the sound which you can set. 
To move to another sound use the EDIT SOUND menu heading the sound 
number and sound name are shown to help obtain the correct sound.

    MENU HEADINGS
    
    FILE 1

    The load and save sounds will load or save single sounds the 
one which is at that time displayed. When selected a normal FILE 
SELECT is displayed with the extender SOU. The extender SOU should 
be added to any of you own files.

    The load and save bank will install or save a bank of 16 
sounds selection is via the standard FILESELECT with the extender 
BAN again you should use this extender on your own files.

    The drive items allow you to choose which drive to use if 
drives C & D are not present then they will not be highlighted.

    For testing the sound on the synthesizer you can press the 
space bar on the ST keyboard the item NOTE TIME will set how long 
the key is pressed. When selected a box with the numbers 1 to 16 
will appear just point to how many seconds you wish the key to be 
pressed. The value currently in use will be highlighted. If you 
don't wish to change the setting just point to the highlighted 
number.

    When the NAME SOUND item is selected you type in the name you 
want and it will appear down at the far bottom right as you type 
press RETURN when complete. The item name under the EDIT SOUND  
menu will be updated as well.

    QUIT is QUIT nothing else to say except make sure you have 
saved any files you are only given one chance to abort QUIT.

    FILE 2 

    VOICE 1 & 2 The only choice is HIGHLIGHTED that is to say you 
cannot select the VOICE you currently in.

    COPY SOUND This will copy the current sound (the one 
displayed) into another area. When selected a box with the numbers 
1 to 16 will be displayed choose where you want it to go.

    CLEAR SOUND will clear the current sound (USE WITH CARE)

    COPY VOICE will copy the current voice into the current SOUNDS 
non displyed voice ie the one not displayed.

    CLEAR VOICE will clear current voice (USE WITH CARE)

    LINE
    This mimics the LINE SELECT on the synthesizer the tick shows 
which voice or voices are selected.

    MODULATION
    This mimics the MODULATION setting on the synthesizer.  If you 
don't  wish  to set RING or NOISE then there should  be  no  ticks 
showing if there is just point to the item which has the tick.

    SET DATA

    DETUNE & VIBRATO these work in the same way when selected a 
box will appear with it's function above it point to the area you 
wish to change hold down the left mouse button and move the mouse 
up or down until the value you require is displayed if you run out 
of screen let the mouse button go and repeat until desired value 
is reached. In the DETUNE box the +/- works just by pointing and 
clicking the mouse button and the symbol toggles. When you set up 
the values you require point to the heading name in the box ie 
DETUNE  or VIBRATO and you will end this function,

    OCTIVE will display the 3 alternatives -1,0,+1 just point and 
click the left mouse button on your selection the current 
selection is highlighted if you don't wish to change the setting 
point to the highlighted box.

    SYTH FILE

    CALL SOUND & CALL BANK willworkonanyofthethreebanks
presentonthesynt.If you want to load just one sound a box with the
numbers 1 to 16 will be displayed choose which you want  to load. 
On CALL BANK all sixteen sounds in abank will be loaded to 
the computer.


    SEND SOUND & SEND BANK will not be highlighted until INTERNAL 
or CARTRIDGE are selected further down this menu heading. This is 
because you cannot change the preset sounds. once you have 
selcected which bank you want SEND SOUND and SEND BANK will be 
highlighted. If you want to send just one sound a box with the 
numbers 1 to 16 will be displayed choose where you want it to go. 
on SEND BANK all sixteen sounds in memory will be downloaded to 
the synthesizer.

    CHANNEL allows you to select which channel you wish to 
transmit data on for most of us no use but if you have more than 
one synthesizer you can select which you send and recive from. 


